    <summary>Depot CLI - build your Docker images in the cloud.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
Depot is a remote container build service that makes building Docker images
faster by offloading work to fast, persistent cloud builders with a fully
managed layer cache.

The `depot` CLI is the official command-line interface for Depot. It supports:

* `depot build` / `depot bake` - build Docker images remotely using Depot's
  cloud infrastructure, a drop-in replacement for `docker build`.
* Native multi-platform builds for `linux/amd64` and `linux/arm64` with no
  emulation.
* Fully-managed, persistent BuildKit cache shared across your team and CI.
* `depot projects`, `depot org`, `depot cache` for managing Depot resources.
* `depot pull` / `depot push` for image registry operations.
* `depot configure-docker` to use Depot as the default Docker builder.
* `depot login` / `depot logout` for authentication.

## Package parameters

This package has no parameters. After install, open a new shell and run:

```
depot --help
depot login
```

## Notes

* This is an unofficial Chocolatey package. The binaries are downloaded
  directly from the official Depot CLI GitHub releases at install time and
  verified with SHA256 checksums. See the VERIFICATION.txt file for details.
* Source code for the Depot CLI is at https://github.com/depot/cli and is
  licensed under the MIT License.
]]></description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/depot/cli/releases/tag/v2.101.47</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
